Crisp and sweet, our Gala Apples are a local favorite, proudly grown in the sunny orchards of California. Their vibrant red and yellow hues make them a standout at our farmer's market, and their delicious, juicy flavor is perfect for fresh snacking or adding a sweet crunch to your salads and pies.

Our California-grown Apples are a staple of our farmer's market, offering a variety of flavors and textures to suit every preference. From the tart Granny Smith to the sweet Fuji, these apples are nurtured by our local farmers, ensuring the freshest and finest quality.

Though not grown locally in California, our ripe and creamy Bananas are carefully selected to bring a tropical touch to our farmer's market. They're the perfect on-the-go snack or addition to your morning smoothie, adding a burst of natural energy and sweetness.

California is renowned for its citrus, and our Oranges are no exception. Sourced from nearby orchards, these oranges are a juicy, sun-kissed delight at our farmer's market. Peel one open to experience the zesty, refreshing taste that only locally grown oranges can provide.

Plump and juicy, our California Strawberries are a true gem at our farmer's market. Grown with care in the state's fertile soil, these strawberries are bursting with sweet, sun-ripened flavor. Enjoy them fresh, in desserts, or as a delightful addition to your salads.

California vineyards are world-famous, and our farmer's market proudly features locally grown Grapes. These plump, sweet clusters are perfect for snacking, sharing, or transforming into fine wines from the heart of California's wine country.

While not native to California, our Pineapples are sourced from top-quality suppliers to offer a taste of the tropics at our farmer's market. Sweet and tangy, they're a refreshing treat that adds a burst of flavor to your dishes.

California's warm sun and fertile soil produce some of the juiciest Watermelons you'll find. At our farmer's market, you can savor the sweet, hydrating goodness of locally grown watermelons, perfect for picnics and summer gatherings.

California's temperate climate is ideal for growing the finest Kiwi fruit. Our farmer's market proudly presents these fuzzy-skinned, emerald-green treasures, offering a tangy-sweet taste and a burst of vitamins to your day.

While not native to California, our Mangoes are carefully sourced to ensure the ripest and most flavorful selection at our farmer's market. Their tropical sweetness and succulent flesh are perfect for enjoying as a snack or adding a taste of the exotic to your dishes.

Grown in California's fertile regions, our Blueberries are a small but mighty delight at our farmer's market. Bursting with antioxidants and flavor, these plump blue gems are perfect for baking, snacking, or adding to your breakfast yogurt.
